This paper discusses privacy concerns in Online Social Networks and proposes a computational model to address them. The paper focuses on the security and privacy aspects of the system, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper deals with social interactions and relationships in Online Social Networks, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. The paper also discusses the changing and implicit nature of contexts in Online Social Networks, which could make it relevant to the cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) category. The paper also discusses the information model and the agent-based approach, which could place it in the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category. Finally, the paper discusses the usability and user experience aspects of the proposed model, which could make it relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category.
